# Security Devices API 🔒

## 📋 Description

This is a Full Stack security devices register, where people can get, add, update and delete security devices. This project aims the Full Stack job interview for Pado's Jr full stack position.

## 🛠️ Technologies

Node.js, Express, MongoDB, Mongoose

## ✅ Prerequisites

Node.js v18+ and npm v8+

## ⚙️ Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   ​`bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd server
​`
2. Install dependencies:
   ​`bash
npm install
​`
3. Configure environment variables:
   ​```bash
   cp .env.example .env

## 🚀 Running the project

-Make sure you are in server folder and then:
npm run dev ("dev": "nodemon index.js")

## 🔑 Environment Variables

DATABASE_URI=your_cluster_link
PORT=3000

## 📡 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint     | Description                                   |
| ------ | ------------ | --------------------------------------------- |
| GET    | /devices     | Get all devices. Filter by type: ?type=camera |
| GET    | /devices/:id | Get an specific device                        |
| POST   | /devices     | Create a device                               |
| PUT    | /devices/:id | Update a device                               |
| DELETE | /devices/:id | Delete a device                               |

## 📁 Project Structure

​`
backend/
  src/
    config/      # Database connection
    controllers/ # Request handlers
    models/      # Mongoose schemas
    routes/      # API routes
  index.js       # Entry point
  .env           # Environment variables
​`
